Certainly! Here's an example of an Expert Advisor in MQL4 that will open a sell order when the RSI indicator goes above a specified threshold (70 in this case).

```mql4
// Define input parameters
extern int RSIPeriod = 14;
extern int RSIThreshold = 70;

// Declare global variables
int sellOrderTicket = 0;

// Expert Advisor start function
void OnTick()
{
    // Calculate RSI value
    double rsiValue = iRSI(Symbol(), 0, RSIPeriod, PRICE_CLOSE, 0);

    // Check if RSI is above threshold
    if (rsiValue > RSIThreshold)
    {
        // Check if no existing sell order is already open
        if (sellOrderTicket == 0)
        {
            // Place a new sell order
            sellOrderTicket = OrderSend(Symbol(), OP_SELL, 1, Bid, 3, 0, 0, "RSI Sell", 0, 0, Red);
            if (sellOrderTicket > 0)
            {
                Print("Sell order placed at ", Bid);
            }
            else
            {
                Print("Failed to place sell order. Error code: ", GetLastError());
            }
        }
    }

    // Check for close conditions of the sell order
    if (sellOrderTicket > 0)
    {
        // Check if the order is closed or partially closed
        if (OrderCloseTime() > 0 || OrderCloseTime() == 0 && OrderLots() < 1)
        {
            sellOrderTicket = 0; // Reset the sell order ticket
            Print("Sell order closed");
        }
    }
}
```

To use this Expert Advisor, follow these steps:

1. Open MetaEditor in MetaTrader.
2. Create a new Expert Advisor.
3. Copy and paste the above code into the Expert Advisor file.
4. Set your desired RSI parameters (RSIPeriod and RSIThreshold) in the input parameters section.
5. Compile the Expert Advisor.
6. Attach the Expert Advisor to a chart in MetaTrader.
7. Make sure that autotrading is enabled.

Please note that this code provides a basic framework and may need further customization or optimization for specific use cases.

